1
00:00:44,967 --> 00:00:47,967
Mommy, is it necessary?

2
00:00:48,033 --> 00:00:50,500
Trust me, Sweetie. I'm a doctor.

3
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:53,867
I need someone
who will take care of her.

4
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:55,433
I'm willing to pay.

5
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,300
This is a big responsibility.

6
00:00:57,367 --> 00:01:00,433
But, Miss, don't you miss
caring for a baby?

7
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,867
Olive, I'm sorry.
I don't mean to pry.

8
00:01:02,933 --> 00:01:05,033
But what is really
Mookie's illness?

9
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:07,567
I still can't determine
specifically

10
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:09,300
what my daughter's illness is.

11
00:01:09,367 --> 00:01:11,167
But have you taken her
to the hospital?

12
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:15,033
Do you think I can't treat and
take care of my child?

13
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:17,167
You didn't finish med school.

14
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:20,333
Well, I know enough
to take care of my daughter.

15
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,133
What's this?
Where did you get this?

16
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:25,767
I got out of the house earlier.

17
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:29,000
Because you disobeyed me,
you'll stay in the dark room.

18
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:30,000
Mommy, no!

19
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:32,867
You know the world outside
is dangerous.

20
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:34,067
You could die.

21
00:01:34,133 --> 00:01:38,067
And as your mother,
I won't let that happen to you.

22
00:01:38,133 --> 00:01:40,900
That's how much I love you.

23
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:05,300
Hush now, my dear.

24
00:02:05,367 --> 00:02:09,600
Come here...

25
00:02:59,767 --> 00:03:03,167
What are you doing here?
My mom might see you.

26
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,967
No.
I'll just give this back to you.

27
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:05,900
You dropped it.

28
00:03:09,933 --> 00:03:12,267
Were you the one singing?

29
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,533
Did you hear that?

30
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:16,833
Yes.

31
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:18,733
You have a very beautiful voice.

32
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:26,000
I heard
you don't leave the house.

33
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,833
Is it because of your
medical condition?

34
00:03:31,067 --> 00:03:32,967
How do you go to school?

35
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:36,267
I'm homeschooled.

36
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:37,133
Really?

37
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:40,533
How do you meet your friends?

38
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,467
I don't have friends.

39
00:03:42,533 --> 00:03:44,167
Just my mom.

40
00:03:44,233 --> 00:03:46,600
You know,
if you go to a regular school,

41
00:03:46,667 --> 00:03:48,433
you'll make many friends.

42
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,367
Kids who are our age.

43
00:03:50,433 --> 00:03:53,500
They also have a lot
of fun activities,

44
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,833
like intrams and field trips.

45
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:58,133
I'm sure you'll enjoy it.

46
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,967
And you can also
join our glee club.

47
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:03,867
You belong there
because your voice is beautiful.

48
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,600
My mom won't allow me.

49
00:04:09,633 --> 00:04:11,000
Because I'm sick.

50
00:04:11,067 --> 00:04:12,133
Mookie!

51
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:16,367
Mookie, it's time
for your medicine.

52
00:04:16,433 --> 00:04:19,167
I have a classmate
who's a cancer patient.

53
00:04:19,233 --> 00:04:21,867
The school doesn't discriminate
against people like you.

54
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:24,867
Really?

55
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:25,900
Yes.

56
00:04:25,967 --> 00:04:29,167
By the way,
I still don't know your name.

57
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:30,300
Mookie!

58
00:04:30,367 --> 00:04:32,167
Who are you talking to?

59
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:33,700
Who are you?

60
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:35,467
Why are you talking
to my daughter?

61
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:42,333
Flor, doesn't our employer
commit child abuse?

62
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:48,000
What mother would do
that to her own child?

63
00:04:48,067 --> 00:04:50,033
Keep your voice down.
Ma'am Olive might hear you.

64
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:52,233
Come on.
Don't you feel bad for Mookie?

65
00:04:54,067 --> 00:04:56,833
Of course, I do.

66
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,333
Who wouldn't?

67
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,033
But what can I do?

68
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:06,067
What if you report her
to the Bantay Bata?

69
00:05:06,133 --> 00:05:07,533
Report her
to a public service program.

70
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,367
Are you out of your mind?

71
00:05:09,433 --> 00:05:11,767
Do you want us to lose our jobs?

72
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:18,167
Poor Mookie.

73
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:28,767
If I were her mother,
I wouldn't mistreat her,

74
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,533
especially since she's sick.

75
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,200
Just stay out of it.

76
00:05:33,267 --> 00:05:35,933
Ma'am Olive knows
what's best for Mookie.

77
00:05:36,867 --> 00:05:38,433
Why are you talking
to my daughter?

78
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,567
Good morning. I'm Zayn.

79
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:43,300
We just moved
in the neighborhood.

80
00:05:44,967 --> 00:05:46,533
Why are you talking
to my daughter?

81
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,467
No, I was just telling
your daughter

82
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:54,300
that she would enjoy
going to a regular school.

83
00:05:54,367 --> 00:05:56,433
I heard she's homeschooled.

84
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,867
How did you know that?

85
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:00,267
Mookie?

86
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:03,667
Do you know him?

87
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:05,767
I don't, Mommy.

88
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,533
It's the first time
I've seen him.

89
00:06:09,767 --> 00:06:14,133
She can join our glee club
if she goes to a regular school.

90
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,900
She belongs there because
she has a beautiful voice.

91
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:23,833
Are you some kind of a creep?

92
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:25,733
Are you stalking my daughter?

93
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,667
No, I don't.

94
00:06:27,733 --> 00:06:29,200
I only heard her singing.

95
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,100
Well...

96
00:06:32,333 --> 00:06:33,433
what right do you have

97
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:37,100
to educate me on how to send
my daughter to school?

98
00:06:37,167 --> 00:06:39,533
Get out of here
before I call the police.

99
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,233
Leave.

100
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,000
I'm sorry.

101
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:02,867
Mookie?

102
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,600
Mommy.

103
00:07:06,667 --> 00:07:08,067
I'll go to the office
real quick.

104
00:07:08,133 --> 00:07:10,800
But I'm gonna be back soon,
okay?

105
00:07:10,867 --> 00:07:12,067
Okay.

106
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:13,767
Go to bed early.

107
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:14,900
Good night.

108
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,467
Good night, Mommy. Be safe.

109
00:09:13,733 --> 00:09:15,433
Maybe I can go here.

110
00:09:16,733 --> 00:09:20,433
I can do it online or on-site.

111
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:25,267
But...

112
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:29,833
Mommy might disagree.

113
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:36,833
Your blood pressure is normal.

114
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,733
120 over 80.

115
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:41,333
Your blood sugar levels
are stable, so that's good.

116
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:45,000
That means your condition
is improving.

117
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:49,600
Well, Mommy, I've been
taking my meds regularly.

118
00:09:49,667 --> 00:09:53,433
And I always eat
vegetables and fruits.

119
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,633
That's good.

120
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:56,533
Yes.

121
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:00,733
Mommy...

122
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:03,600
Yes, Dear?

123
00:10:03,667 --> 00:10:07,333
Since my condition
is improving...

124
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:11,800
if you will let me, maybe...

125
00:10:13,167 --> 00:10:15,433
can I go to a regular school?

126
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:21,500
Regular school?

127
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:23,500
Yes.

128
00:10:38,467 --> 00:10:41,033
Is that how that man
influences you?

129
00:10:42,467 --> 00:10:44,067
Do you like him?

130
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:48,333
Do you want to flirt with him?

131
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,533
No, Mommy.

132
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,533
I don't like him.

133
00:10:52,967 --> 00:10:53,967
Then why?

134
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,567
Why, all of a sudden...

135
00:10:57,567 --> 00:10:59,300
do you want to go
to a regular school?

136
00:11:02,167 --> 00:11:07,267
Because all my life,
I've been homeschooled.

137
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:11,467
I'm now 17 years old.

138
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:15,100
I'm going to be an adult soon.

139
00:11:18,033 --> 00:11:24,900
I want to know how it feels
to be in the outside world.

140
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:29,733
The feeling of being
a normal teenager.

141
00:11:32,933 --> 00:11:35,567
But you're not like
any other teenager.

142
00:11:36,667 --> 00:11:37,900
You're not normal.

143
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,967
Just because your vital stats
are stable

144
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:44,733
doesn't mean you're healed.

145
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,900
You're still weak.

146
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:49,033
So, I'm so sorry, Dear.

147
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:51,800
But you will never go
to a regular school.

148
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:57,867
But Mommy, they have programs
for students like me.

149
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:59,400
I said no.

150
00:12:01,933 --> 00:12:03,133
You're not going anywhere
but here.

151
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,867
What? Aren't you going anywhere?

152
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:54,000
Mom, no one will take care
of Baby Samantha.

153
00:12:54,067 --> 00:12:56,333
Poor baby.

154
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,733
How cute.

155
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:16,667
Emma.

156
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,300
Don't you want
to conceive again?

157
00:13:22,767 --> 00:13:23,467
Mom?

158
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,167
Where did it come from?

159
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,767
Look at yourself.

160
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:34,167
You enjoy taking care of a child
who's not related to you.

161
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:38,000
Mom, someone doesn't need
to be our relative

162
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,900
for us to love her, right?

163
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:42,767
It's better
if it's your own blood.

164
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:44,200
Your own child.

165
00:13:45,633 --> 00:13:48,800
Haven't you and Danilo talked
about having a baby again?

166
00:13:50,467 --> 00:13:56,133
Mom, we've tried several times,
but we couldn't conceive.

167
00:13:56,233 --> 00:14:00,367
The doctor said I have a problem
with my uterus.

168
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:01,433
She said maybe it's because

169
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:04,067
of the stress of
what happened to Kayla.

170
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,600
Too bad.

171
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:10,467
The one who deserves
to be a mother

172
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:12,467
isn't blessed with a child.

173
00:14:14,267 --> 00:14:15,733
While others...

174
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,700
don't deserve to be one.

175
00:14:23,733 --> 00:14:24,433
What's wrong?

176
00:14:25,667 --> 00:14:27,133
Why aren't you eating?

177
00:14:28,767 --> 00:14:30,233
Don't you have an appetite?

178
00:14:35,633 --> 00:14:36,467
What is it?

179
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,967
Does your stomach ache?

180
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:43,633
No, Mommy.

181
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:49,333
So, why aren't you eating?

182
00:14:50,867 --> 00:14:56,167
Why aren't you letting me
go to a regular school?

183
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:03,467
I'll do everything you want.

184
00:15:04,433 --> 00:15:06,533
I'll study hard.

185
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:10,533
And I'll go home early
after school.

186
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,533
I'll go straight home after.

187
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,900
Why are you...

188
00:15:15,567 --> 00:15:17,833
so stubborn?

189
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:20,200
Didn't I tell you
that you can't?

190
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:25,133
I just want to...

191
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:28,033
You want to go back
to the dark room?

192
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:29,600
Is that what you want?

193
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:38,267
I only want to go
to a regular school, Mommy.

194
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:46,400
I do everything you say.
I'm a good girl, am I not?

195
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:54,233
But, Mommy, why do you seem like
you don't want me to be happy?

196
00:15:54,300 --> 00:15:55,700
Stop it!

197
00:15:57,367 --> 00:16:04,100
You know, the mommies
in the series I watch,

198
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:09,033
mothers do everything
for their children.

199
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:16,933
But, Mommy, why do you seem like
you don't want me to be happy?

200
00:16:18,533 --> 00:16:28,500
Why can't I feel
your love for me?

201
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,333
I said stop it!

202
00:16:32,267 --> 00:16:35,033
How dare you question
my love for you!

203
00:16:55,367 --> 00:16:59,033
I went out of the house earlier.

204
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:00,500
I tripped.

205
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:02,933
You went out?

206
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,900
If you will let me, maybe...

207
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,567
can I go to a regular school?

208
00:17:09,633 --> 00:17:12,367
Is that the influence
that man had on you?

209
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:18,233
The mothers do everything
for their children.

210
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:23,100
But why do you seem like you
don't want me to be happy?

211
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:33,733
Why can't I feel
your love for me?

212
00:18:17,733 --> 00:18:18,667
Mookie.

213
00:18:19,767 --> 00:18:20,600
Sweetie.

214
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,333
Mookie, I'm so sorry.

215
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:36,167
I shouldn't have done that.

216
00:18:40,167 --> 00:18:43,833
I know, you're already 17.

217
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:47,533
You're growing, and...

218
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:50,767
there's nothing I can do
about it.

219
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:53,633
I was wrong

220
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:59,367
because I shouldn't deprive
you of things you want to do...

221
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:06,533
especially something as simple
as going to a regular school.

222
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:13,533
But you know what?

223
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:15,800
Lately...

224
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:19,933
you've been such a good girl

225
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,233
whenever you're taking
your medicine.

226
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,200
So...

227
00:19:28,133 --> 00:19:29,867
yes.

228
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:31,300
Really?

229
00:19:33,367 --> 00:19:38,567
I'm letting you enroll
in a regular school.

230
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:49,467
I'm letting you enroll
in a regular school.

231
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,567
Really, Mommy?

232
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:57,733
So stop crying.

233
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:01,000
Okay?

234
00:20:02,167 --> 00:20:04,100
Thank you.

235
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:05,467
Thank you, Mommy.

236
00:20:07,433 --> 00:20:09,067
But first...

237
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:15,167
What's that for?

238
00:20:16,867 --> 00:20:19,467
This is for your immune system.

239
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:23,700
So that when you go to school,
you're healthy and strong.

240
00:20:24,867 --> 00:20:26,467
Okay?

241
00:20:26,533 --> 00:20:27,700
Okay.

242
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:29,500
Pull down your pajamas.

243
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:38,233
Okay.

244
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:47,733
A little more.

245
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:50,033
That's it.

246
00:20:54,033 --> 00:20:55,133
Good girl.

247
00:20:57,633 --> 00:20:58,400
Okay.

248
00:21:00,633 --> 00:21:02,533
I think you should rest now.

249
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,333
We're early tomorrow.

250
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,767
Okay, Mommy.

251
00:21:11,967 --> 00:21:13,233
There you go.

252
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:17,967
Okay.

253
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:22,900
There.

254
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,767
Good night, Mommy.

255
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:27,267
Good night, Dear.

256
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:30,433
I will see you tomorrow.

257
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:31,767
Sweet dreams.

258
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,100
Good night.

259
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:49,433
What happened?

260
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:52,200
Why can't I move my legs?

261
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:08,900
Mommy! Mommy!

262
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:10,800
- Mommy!
- Mookie!

263
00:23:10,867 --> 00:23:13,133
- Ma'am, what happened?
- Mookie! What happened?

264
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:14,500
Why are you on the floor?

265
00:23:14,567 --> 00:23:15,900
- Mookie!
- Oh my God! Mookie!

266
00:23:15,967 --> 00:23:17,467
Mommy!

267
00:23:17,533 --> 00:23:18,800
What happened?

268
00:23:18,867 --> 00:23:22,800
Mommy! Mommy!
I can't move my legs, Mommy!

269
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:25,033
I can't move my legs!

270
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:29,633
I don't know why!
I don't know why!

271
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:32,133
- What's happening, Mommy?
- It's okay.

272
